2026-04-13 15:43:49,209 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: The workbook has a single sheet with header text in A1, B1, and C1. The instruction asks for a formula in C1 that sums A1 and B1 only when both cells contain values (i.e., are not empty). We will write an IF+AND formula that checks for non‑blank cells and otherwise returns an empty string. Then we will save the modified workbook to the output directory using the same filename.
Code:
```repl
import os
import openpyxl

# Paths
input_path = input_spreadsheet
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet"
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, os.path.basename(input_path))

# Ensure output directory exists
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Load workbook (read/write)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]  # first sheet

# Write the conditional sum formula into C1
# Formula: =IF(AND(A1<>"",B1<>""),A1+B1,"")
ws["C1"] = "=IF(AND(A1<>\"\",B1<>\"\"),A1+B1,\"\")"

# Save the modified workbook
wb.save(output_path)
```
