2026-04-13 15:45:35,288 INFO RLM iteration 4/50
Reasoning: The previous formula `=IF(AND(A1<>"",B1<>""),A1+B1,"")` caused a #VALUE! error because A1 and B1 contain text headers, not numeric values. To avoid errors, we should check that both cells contain numbers (dates are stored as numbers in Excel) before adding them. The formula `=IF(AND(ISNUMBER(A1),ISNUMBER(B1)),A1+B1,"")` will return the sum only when both cells are numeric, otherwise it returns an empty string. We'll replace the existing C1 content with this formula, recalculate, and verify that C1 is blank (since the header row contains text). Finally, we'll submit the modified spreadsheet.
Code:
```repl
import os, openpyxl

# Paths
input_path = input_spreadsheet
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet"
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, os.path.basename(input_path))

# Ensure output directory exists
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Load workbook (read/write)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]  # first sheet

# Write the conditional sum formula into C1, checking for numeric values
ws["C1"] = '=IF(AND(ISNUMBER(A1),ISNUMBER(B1)),A1+B1,"")'

# Save the modified workbook
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas in the saved workbook
recalc_result = await recalculate(output_path)
print("Recalc result:", recalc_result)

# Load the workbook with data_only to read cached formula results
wb_data = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_data = wb_data[wb_data.sheetnames[0]]

# Print the computed value of C1 after recalculation
print("C1 computed value after recalc:", ws_data["C1"].value)
```
